description:
&lt;p&gt;We are inviting applications for the position of Bank Staff Nurse, reporting to the POA Manager to join the POA team based at Pinehill.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the global Ramsay Health Care Group, Pinehill Hospital is one of Hertfordshire’s leading private hospitals with an excellent reputation for delivering high quality patient-centred care. We provide a wide range of elective healthcare services to private and NHS patients. Rated ‘Good’ by the CQC, Pinehill Hospital is proud of the high quality clinical standards we provide to our patients and we are committed to ensuring that we can continuously improve the standards of services we provide.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake pre-operative assessment of patients awaiting elective surgery across all specialities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The key focus is to ensure that patients are prepared physically and psychologically for a planned operative procedure, ensuring appropriate information provision and identifying potential discharge concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The applicant is expected to be a role model for junior staff and student nurses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be an accountable practitioner, taking every opportunity to sustain and improve knowledge and professional competence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To provide support to the PAC Lead in effectively leading and managing the PAC department.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential experience and qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered with the NMC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to work in a team or independently as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to use own initiative and take charge of the PAC department / deputise for the PAC Lead in their absence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible and committed to maintaining and improving patient experience and able to adapt to change as we continue to develop our service to meet the needs of our patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiastic / promoting positive attitude at work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates a good working knowledge &amp; compliance with Ramsay Policies and CQC Standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sound written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility and adaptability to meet the changing needs of the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated Customer Service skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated Computer Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ramsay Way &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ramsay Health Care is committed to being a leading provider of health care services by delivering high quality outcomes for patients and ensuring long term profitability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are caring, progressive, enjoy our work and use a positive spirit to succeed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We take pride in our achievements and actively seek new ways of doing better&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We value integrity, credibility and respect for the individual&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We build constructive relationships to achieve positive outcomes for all&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We believe that success comes through recognising and encouraging the value of people and teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We aim to grow our business whiles maintaining sustainable level of profitability, providing a basis for stakeholder loyalty.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary – depending on skills and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributory pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days’ annual leave plus the opportunity to buy/sell more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible shift options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free onsite parking and a subsidised staff restaurant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free uniform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to our employee Discount Programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;* Salary based on base plus some enhancements for working some weekends or nights&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
